<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-06-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-06-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="296" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d296">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/5642:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé in France (<persName type="to">Tuck</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-09">June 9,
                                    1942</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>364. Your 806, June 4, 5 p.m. The Department has been giving urgent
                                consideration to resumption of the North African economic program
                                and a decision is expected shortly. You may convey this information
                                informally to the appropriate French authorities.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>